docker run is used to create a new container and start it from a Docker image.
docker run [options] <image>
docker run -d nginx
docker run -d --name my-nginx nginx

If you want to access Nginx from your computer:
docker run -d --name my-nginx -p 8080:80 nginx
-p HOST_PORT:CONTAINER_PORT

You can see all containers, including stopped ones:
docker ps -a

To permanently remove a stopped container:
docker rm my-nginx
force-remove a running container:
docker rm -f my-nginx

docker stop jenkins
docker start jenkins

docker rm jenkins
The container is deleted, but your Jenkins image and Docker volume are not automatically deleted.

Here:

-i = keep stdin open
-t = allocate a terminal (TTY)
-it = interactive terminal

So, for interactive containers, you usually use:
docker run -it <image>


  
